all_lizards.csv: the occurrence records of Phrynocephalus vlangalii
Sources:Collected:The data collected from literature/GBIF/and other field work
Pop: Low:high-elevation population <3600 m asl High:Extra-high-elevation population >3600 m asl

BM_all.csv: the body mass of P.vlangalii
Elevation: the elevation of lizards 
Sex:the gender of the lizards
SVL: the snout-vent length of lizards(cm)
BM: the body mass of lizards (g)

CTm.csv: the thermal tolerance of vlangalii
Elevation: the elevation of lizards 
Sex:the gender of the lizards
SVL: the snout-vent length of lizards(cm)
BM: the body mass of lizards (g)
CTmin:the critical thermal minimum of lizards (℃)
CTmax:the critical thermal maximum of lizards (℃)

Lizard_traits.csv: the parameter inputted in NicheMapR
Ele：the elevation of three site
Ww_g:  Wet weight of animal (g)
T_Fmin: Minimum foraging temperature, °C (also affects burrow depth selection)
T_F_max: Maximum foraging temperature, °C
T_B_min:Minimum basking temperature, °C
T_RB_min:Minimum temperature at which animal will move from retreat to basking site, °C
T_pref:Preferred body temperature, °C
CT_max:Critical thermal maximum, °C (affects burrow depth selection and may be used to impose death from heat stress)
CT_min:Critical thermal minimum, °C (affects burrow depth selection and may be used to impose death from cold stress)
M_1: Metabolic rate parameter 1 V_O2=M_1*M^M_2*10^(M_3*Tb), in ml O2 / h, default parameters for lizards based on Eq. 2 from Andrews & Pough 1985. Physiol. Zool. 58:214-231
M_2:Metabolic rate parameter 2
M_3:Metabolic rate parameter 3

MR_submit.csv:The metabolic rate data of P.vlangalii
Elevation: the elevation of lizards 
Sex:the gender of the lizards
Tbody: the body temperatures when we measured the resting metabolic rate
BM: the body mass of lizards (g)
V_ml_g_h: resting metabolic rate (CO2 production rate:ml/g/h)
V_ml_h: resting metabolic rate (CO2 production rate:ml/h)

Tsel_submit.csv: The selected body temperature of P.vlangalii
Elevation: the elevation of lizards 
SVL: the snout-vent length of lizards(cm)
BM: the body mass of lizards (g)
Sex:the gender of the lizards
Gravid: whether lizard is pregnant or not
Tsel:the select body temperatures 

Tbody.csv: the active body temperatures of P.vlangalii
Year:the year we measured the data
Date:the date we measured the data
Elevation: the elevation of lizards
Time: the time we measured the data (hour)
Sex:the gender of the lizards
SVL: the snout-vent length of lizards(cm)
Tbody:the active body temperatures
Gravid: whether lizard is pregnant or not
Tsurface: the surface temperatures when we measured the body temperatures
Tair:the air temperatures when we measured the body temperatures

lizard_traits.R: analyze the physiological data
Liz_mod_microglo.R: calculate the ecophysiological responses
